### What each test class verifies

| Class | Requirement coverage |
|---|---|
| `TestOwnOrganisationAccess` | Privacy-officer **can** read logs scoped to their own organisation; correct data is returned; repository is called with the right org ID. |
| `TestCrossOrganisationAccessForbidden` | Cross-organisation access raises `PermissionDeniedError`; the repository is **never queried** before the guard fires; parametrised over multiple foreign orgs. |
| `TestRoleBasedAccessControl` | Non-privacy-officer roles (employee, admin, …) are denied even for their own org; role check happens **before** any repository call. |
| `TestEdgeCases` | Non-existent logs, empty/None org IDs, isolation between two officers from different orgs. |
